were decidedly proud of their practice of animal husbandry and allowed for their animals to enjoy free range grazing, sunlight, shade, warmth, care, throughout their lives. This was a source of pride for farmers. I am glad these people have been exposed and quite saddened that this is not so very rare. Factory farming eradicated the small farmer and for my part, the small farmer did a much better job. Both the animals and the farmer were happier in those days. Smaller is better from farming to government. It's more manageable and more directly accountable. Thank you for this petition.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Corinne  Conley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26920060"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T22:50:20Z","content":"This needs to be banned, if for no other reason than to promote humanity.  How any human being can kill like this is beyond me.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Donna Cassano","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/564944"},{"created_at":"2012-12-16T22:52:56Z","content":"It's for this exact reason of animal cruelty that I became a vegetarian. Not because of the health benefits, not because of the expense but because I was shocked to see how most meat comes to our plates and how unaware or ignorant we choose to be towards it. I can happily say that letting go of meat was  one of the best decisions I decided to take and how almost 4 years later, I have never regretted it one second. :)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Beba B","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10570725"},{"created_at":"2013-04-18T18:00:40Z","content":"While doing a school project i came across this video and i was appaulled!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nash Skrzypek","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/47905852"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T16:53:22Z","content":"I will not buy meat from retailers that do not support the welfare of animals.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Kraw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8733794"},{"created_at":"2012-12-27T19:25:48Z","content":