ount":0,"author_name":"Gary Greenwood","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34319784"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T15:30:48Z","content":"All living creatures should be treated with kindness and dignity. This is appalling.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Arian Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10197885"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T20:16:51Z","content":"A few years ago I raised two beautiful hogs in a free range pasture environment. They would graze the grass, enjoy the sun, sky, buck and leap.  Fed organic mash 2 X/day, and treated very well. I never got them back from the slaughter house. WHY, you ask.  They said the CFI didn't pass them. What B.S because I know they were healthy. I insisted on talking to the plant vet. that said he didn't even see them, but his signature was on the paperwork (illegal). He refered to them as boutique meat, and said they may have not been to standard. I said you can't compare these athletes to the couch potatoes of the industry. As far as I'm concerened, SOMEONE STOLE MY QUALITY ANIMALS!  They don't want society to have access to quality raised pork/meat. I cannot legally sell to the public without the CFI inspection stamp. Sorry general society, my meat has to stay in the family from now on. (Small farmer raising animals as your great grandfathers did.)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lucy gozen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28204193"},{"created_at":"2012-12-29T21:47:24Z","content":"this is sick, and this has to stop! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marysah Yaworski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27814396"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T15:37:22Z","content":"Because all living things deserve the right to live without being tortured. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Meg Kwas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/460168"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T23:19:47Z","content":"I abhor violence. It makes all of us less human. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Gjertsen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/370909"},{"c