ntent":"  I am disgusted and appalled after reading the article on the abuses taking place at the Puratone factory farm that supplies Sobeys stores which is where I shop on a regular basis and always believed Sobeys to be an ethical company. I will no longer support a store that indirectly engages or supports this horrific unethical cruelty. \r\nRoss Davis","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ross Davis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31749670"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T20:13:04Z","content":"no animal should go through that type of existence.  They give their life to feed people at least they can be appreciated for that if not more! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Wilma Lamarche","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34750904"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T17:25:43Z","content":"I am a vegetarian and have not eaten pork for many years. The treatment of pigs in the meat industry shows no respect for these intelligent creatures.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erin McDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9176410"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T00:47:44Z","content":"For our health and health of farm animals","like_count":0,"author_name":"kate moore","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30793476"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T02:30:39Z","content":"This is just so cruel and horrible I can't even begin to tell you how sick I feel. These helpless animals at the mercy of cruel humans.  Thank you for doing this and exposing the horror.  There is non so blind as those who will not see! I rarely ate pork but stopped completely over 3 years ago. I now sponsor a pig at a sanctuary in Ontario. She escaped this awful fate and leads a happy life free from fear and abuse.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nora  Lynch","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17315233"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T10:56:49Z","content":"Because I love animals, and I consider them to be equals with us human beings.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carlos Ku King","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29937328"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T17:39:12Z","content":"Mankinds cruelty is not acceptable to truely civalized beings!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ken Klug","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20265124"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:41:46Z","content":"I was aware of the cruelty these sentient beings are subjected to just to provide people with bacon & pork products. Vegans are living proof that we do not need animal protein to live a healthy lifestyle. This is inhumane & it needs to stop immediately.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Anita  Virginillo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3311683"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T20:19:42Z","content":"it is just plain cruel and inhumane, we should all be accountable.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rowena Cruz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36311910"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T16:11:43Z","content":"Cruelty to animals is never acceptable, and always unnecessary.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carrie Lyle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24394600"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T00:48:39Z","content":"It is cruel","like_count":0,"author_name":"russell etienne","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24313957"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:14:24Z","content":"Even if we are raising animals for consumption, we need to ensure that their existences are lived under humane conditions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorne Warwick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2441986"},{"created_at":"2013-03-22T00:25:01Z","content":"Animal suffering is the same as human suffering.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michael Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/44902454"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T03:50:07Z","content":"back to natural behavior of the pig","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marcel Plamondon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8205526"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:34:05Z","content":"I'm a vegetarian and I don't believe any animal should be consumed, let alone be raised in such horrific conditions.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Iorio","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27739728"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:46:57Z","content":"totaly insane","like_count":0,"author_name":"louis barrette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31206801"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:53:15Z","content":"Put the CEOs in cages for a few days!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jim Harrison","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37011530"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:38:08Z","content":"It is unethical and cruel to treat animals this way.  THINK about it. Why torment any animal?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Frances Higginson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/4978983"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T19:01:54Z","content":"I am opposed to the cruel treatment of animals in factory farms.","like_count":0,"author_name":"john irving","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31754409"},{"created_at":"2013-01-11T22:56:05Z","content":"Treat animals with respect. Pigs are some of the most intelligent animals.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Ann Regnier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29313547"},{"created_at":"2012-12-15T17:37:41Z","content":"Animals are important to us humans & we should treat them with a level of respect that they so richly deserve.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Steve Wilson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22884019"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T22:12:43Z","content":"pigs are such lovely animals how could you treat them like this?","like_count":0,"author_name":"karen hemmings","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37040061"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T15:48:28Z","content":"Animals raised for food are not heads of lettuce. They deserve to be treated humanely and live their short lives in a healthy and as natural  manner as possible. Consumers are becoming increasingly aware of the terrible \"factory\" farming methods used in producing foods for the consumer market and don't like what they are learning. Most consumers care how their food  is produced, in this case pork , and are willing to reduce or eliminate meats that have been sourced from animals raised under these stressful confined conditions. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathryn Heinisch","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1442251"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T00:07:29Z","content":"I'm signing this petition because it discusts me that these creatures have to grow up living in the conditions they currently live in. Yes we use these animals as a food source, but we don't have to succumb to this sort of inhumaine behaviour. As human beings we should feel empathy and compassion for the living creatures who share this planet with us. They deserve dignity and freedom also, even if their end is excellorated for our personal gain. You can't spell livestock with out live and living is not defined by or include these conditions. Happy animals in turn translate to a better product, and a better product translates to better health for us. Let these animals live with dignity so that we can live healthier when we consume them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chris Martinez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24336170"},{"created_at":"2013-02-02T17:55:09Z","content":"There's a quote that says roughly \"The way to judge a society is by how it treats its poor, it's prisoners, and it's animals.\" If this is a test, we're failing. Why is being born in a less intelligent species a reason to be tortured and confined until death? Animal rights laws aren't good enough yet. Animals still suffer for the sake of efficiency and monetary gain. If there was ever reason for an animal to suffer, that is the worst. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julia Jaynes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/40381321"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T17:44:17Z","content":"Because no animal should be abused and tortured; treating these pigs like this is beyond horrific.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Diane Hershfield","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2456997"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T22:12:42Z","content":"This issue is important because we, as consumers can make a difference in the lives of these animals. We cannot expect that people will necessarily stop eating meat, but we can certainly demand that the animals who give their lives for our consumption live their lives free of pain and neglect. The pain and suffering of these animals is not necessary and we need to be more aware or where our food sources come from.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sandra Hori","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24081376"},{"created_at":"2013-05-11T23:54:50Z","content":"Animals deserve to be treated humanely, they have no voice, which is why we need to do everything possible to protect them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ayesha Menezes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50311172"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T22:50:47Z","content":"These are sentient beings. There would be no difference if you kept your mothers penned up like this to breed and whacked your brothers and sisters to death if they had a mole. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kathleen Nesbitt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36953086"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T00:22:52Z","content":"Small sustainable farms are being obliterated by these massive animal factories.  Until consumers own the fact that their choice to select food by price and quantity over quality and sustainability is not only affecting their own bodies, but the ailing planet as a whole - then this will be a very long fight.  As a small farmer myself, I'm in for the long haul -  KNOW YOUR FARMER!! and cheers to the battle.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paula Cassidy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27921765"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T21:20:21Z","content":"A shocking way to treat any living creature for whatever  reason.  Are the people who gravitate to these places to  'look after' these animals naturally evil, or do they become so?  In places like these concentration camps, the animals' characters soar far above the dreadful humans who do nothing but display their rotten characters by attacking the weak and helpless for no reason at all.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Deirdre Balaam","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2071861"},{"created_at":"2012-12-12T22:56:53Z","content":"It's torture! Ouch, I mean...seriously? It's sociopathic. What kind of food does a tortured piglet become anyway?","like_count":0,"author_name":"allison ratner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/292534"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:20:34Z","content":"I think that animals should have a comfortable and natural life. We are not going to make the world into vegans, but we can at least take care of the animals that will be raised for meat. I also don't like the growth hormones and corn being fed to animals to make them fatten up faster. No wonder we are so unhealthy. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Holly O'Neill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26675048"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:48:07Z","content":"Totalignoranceof these pracrices. Are there any humane pork processing companies?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jane Wentzell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28731272"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:09:40Z","content":"I recently made the decision to become vegetarian after learning about the maltreatment of animals. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Courtney Scanlan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7888386"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:22:45Z","content":"I choose to be vegetarian because the raising of animals for food offends me personally.  I do not wish to impose my views on anyone else.  At the same time, we cannot be evolved human beings while we are treating the animals that we raise for food in an inhumane manner.  This is about profit, not about nourishing people.  It has to stop.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelly Williamson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35227739"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:28:19Z","content":"While I think it is up to the indivdual to choose weather or not to eat meat- it is our responsibility to 