e treatment that these animals have to endure","like_count":0,"author_name":"Judy Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1586255"},{"created_at":"2012-12-12T04:23:43Z","content":"I just want to say thank you to \"Darrel\" for being so brave and courageous.  This madness needed exposure.  Canadians need to know.  I just hope there will be enough hype about this to create change.  I know you've changed how we eat in our house.  Thanks again from me and from the animals.  You gave them a voice.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sabrina Brodie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12935958"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T15:48:46Z","content":"Pigs are incredibly smart and aware. They are probably the most intelligent of all domestic animals. No animal should be confined in such a small area and with such uncaring cruelty but especially these intelligent creatures. If it is cruel to treat dogs this way then it is just as cruel if not more so to treat pigs this way.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Melinda Wiltshire-Gibson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26825239"},{"created_at":"2012-12-27T11:31:35Z","content":"It's obvious why.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jaros\u0142aw Jask\u00f3lski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34290890"},{"created_at":"2013-02-28T00:30:29Z","content":"My daughter is very passionate about this stuff. It's wrong..","like_count":0,"author_name":"Dieter Schaefer Schaefer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42392522"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T16:30:03Z","content":"no animal should never, ever be treated cruely.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Charon Mahoney","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10111520"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T23:25:57Z","content":"Je veux que les animaux soient trait\u00e9 comme des humains!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Erik Tremblay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36324358"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T00:20:37Z","content":"A life is a life.  We all deserve respect!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rachelle  Depratto","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2481237"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:12:00Z","content":"I have been a vegetarian since the age of 6 as I am against any form of animal cruelty. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maighdlyn Lussier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33045936"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:49:21Z","content":"I unwisely visited a slaughterhouse once and from that day became a vegetarian. The cruelty has to stop. What we're doing to animals is sub-human.","like_count":0,"author_name":"W. John Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35855799"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:39:42Z","content":"xvx","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alexei Tarnopolski","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13644382"},{"created_at":"2013-01-26T03:05:40Z","content":"I believe animal rights are very inportant","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex Wortman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33887588"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T04:37:17Z","content":"I love animals, so it disgusts and horrifies me when they are being tortured, abused, and murdered. That we sanction this treatment under the umbrella of \"food production\" only serves to sicken me further. There is no need to consume animals to survive, and there is certainly no reason to treat animals the way these poor pigs are being treated. STOP using gestation crates! STOP mutilating piglets without anesthetic! STOP eating animals! The time has come for COMPASSION!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natalie Broadfield","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1998761"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:25:30Z","content":"There is no earthly reason to allow this to happen to the animals. Whatever happened to good animal husbandry??? This appears to be what happens when we allow big business to do farming and it all becomes a money oriented thing not responsible farming.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jane Carr","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26807559"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T17:33:28Z","content":"Pigs are sentient beings and we can no longer allow this cruel treatment. I would pay double for humanely raised/slaughtered pork products. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorry-Ann Austin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9599487"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T03:10:45Z","content":"Is this the same pig that was in Charlotte's Web?  \r\nSo cruel!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cassandra Hanrahan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1623450"},{"created_at":"2012-12-31T16:00:11Z","content":"Disgusting practices!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shirley Tuite","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37776446"},{"created_at":"2013-03-07T19:51:03Z","content":"How can anybody, with a conscience, enjoy eating their meal - when their \"meal\". has been tortured before \"turning up\" on their plate/??!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"carol gover","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43353226"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T01:43:07Z","content":"The way animals are treated before they wind up in our supermarkets is nothing short of abhorrent. It is so bad, in fact, that despite living on a student non-income and raising two children with little child support, I will NOT buy meat from regular supermarkets. I would rather go almost entirely without, and only eat more expensive, cruelty-free meat now and then, than contribute to the barbaric, unethical practices that are currently used throughout N. America. Laws need to be passed to stop this NOW! Each one of the animals that is killed between now and the day when this is banned is a living, breathing creature with the ability to feel every bit of pain and fear inflicted upon it as acutely as any other living creature. It is barbaric, and yes, the stores buying the products need to take responsibility for it; waiting for the government to get off it's unethical ass and do something about it is not an acceptable option.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Megan Smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17217536"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T17:41:52Z","content":"I could not purchase meat from facilities who participated in such cruelty.  I will not be purchasing anything from any of your stores until I hear that you have pledged not to carry meat from plants that sustain such practices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"hollie tutchener","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28868753"},{"created_at":"2012-12-29T20:02:52Z","content":"I am a veterinarian and a vegetarian.  Having a cheap, abundant meat supply is not justification enough for the inhumane treatment of our food animals.  Meat consumption is not a necessity to live.  If people want the \"luxury\" of meat it should be priced so as to allow its production in a respectful and humane manner, regardless of whether or not the humane treatment of food animals is important to the people eating them.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle Lareau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37686365"},{"created_at":"2013-01-02T00:43:22Z","content":"being cruel  to any animals is sooo wrong...","like_count":0,"author_name":"gary montgomery","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16221282"},{"created_at":"2013-01-29T04:01:02Z","content":"I took a class on \"ethics on what you eat\" and it has definitely opened my eyes. No sentient being should have to suffer and animals in the industrial agriculture are treated in disgusting ways and this has to end!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lizane Proietti","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25690903"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T16:26:15Z","content":"would u like to live like that if this was an everyday farmer spca would be all over them for cruelty and there is no need for it","like_count":0,"author_name":"barb clark","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36594964"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T21:33:26Z","content":"Now I see both the US and Canada treat pigs horribly.  Please, please stop this cruelty.  Every injury inflicted on these animals is one more void in your humanity--please reverse this course before you have none left.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Palmer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24158579"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T02:14:17Z","content":"I care about animals","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cassidy Tan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37113060"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:51:22Z","content":"Because no where in the rest of the world this cruelty is legal and I am shocked that any one with right mind kind justify this!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Franzi Cassidy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12779103"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:42:43Z","content":"Is it so difficult to treat animasl with decency?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chantal Piquette","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27408458"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T02:54:55Z","content":"Because it represents my core values. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debra Swinimer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36191391"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T22:45:15Z","content":"Animals such as pigs are intelligent sentient creatures with a nervous sytem equivalent to our own. They suffer pain as we do. They react to stress and deprivation as we do. It is the 21st century for god's sake and no one should be making money out of industry such as this which  allows such extreme cruelty and human induced suffering to be perpetuated against such an intelligent and sensitive creature, or any other living creature. The workers in this industry are sadists and the owners of this factory are morally bankrupt  for making money out of such suffering.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ann  Beatty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28764881"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T22:46:49Z","content":"Being decent to aniimals is much more important than profits from the  meat industry. IT is as someone said, barbaric to treat them this way - intelligent creatures!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barbara Neyedly","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7967147"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T16:37:06Z","content":"These animals didn't consent to this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cynthia Crawford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35118816"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T01:03:03Z","content":"I used to shop a lot at Superstore, but in the past few years a rarely go - largely because I cannot buy humanely raised meat there.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stephen Stewart","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22339593"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T04:13:54Z","content":"How would you like it if pigs kept us in cages and grinded us up slowly.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alex McDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13382954"},{"created_at":"2012-12-23T17:59:05Z","content":"How would you like to be confined for mins, hours, days, months...  This is 'convenient cruelty' and disgusting.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Peter E Davenport","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13970141"},{"created_at":"2013-01-25T03:49:31Z","content":"As someone aspiring to be a veterinarian, I have a love for animals of any kind and seeing them abused in any way makes me sick. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cherlyne Wong","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20029460"},{"created_at":"2013-01-29T03:23:35Z","content":"It is important to me as a consumer that the animals raised for food are kept in appropriate living conditions that is condicive to their health and well being. We will not purchase ANY of these pork products until this deplorrable situation is changed.","like_count":0,"author_name":"s. andrun","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33845801"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T23:36:16Z","content":"I can't say I'll stop eating pork, but can say I'll switch now to buying pork from sources that can at least treat them humanely.  They're giving their life for us, we can at least keep them comfortable, no?   I don't think it's too much to ask ... or DEMAND!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tammy Gallacher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21170423"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T10:34:17Z","content":"I ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Monica Arora","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27511918"},{"created_at":"2012-12-25T13:19:44Z","content":"\u201cUnless someone like you cares a whole awful lot, nothing is going to get better. It's not.\u201d\r\nDr. Suess","like_count":0,"author_name":"Simon Fraser","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35724668"},{"created_at":"2012-12-25T21:02:04Z","content":"Why do we keep hurting animals? Because we keep thinking that we are superior to them. This way of thinking has to change.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Alyssa Symons-B\u00e9langer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26374742"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:16:50Z","content":"Why is this important to me?  It should be important to everyone.  IT'S JUST PLAIN WRONG!  No longer can we just assuage our guilt and say \"it's only an animals - it doesn't feel\".  It's sentient, it feels pain and suffering JUST LIKE WE DO!  How dare we assume we have the right to torture them like this.  Please stop.  If people have to eat meat, do the slaughter in a humane way, much like we put down a domestic pet.  I'm sick and tired of this.  Crushed by humanity's lack of care.  Damn right it's important to me!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan  Munro","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27140551"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:49:25Z","content":"I have always been appalled by the crating system for pigs but didn't realize that other countries are way ahead of us on this.  Thank you for this chance to speak out.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Harpur","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36085356"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:28:45Z","content":"Please stop buying and selling meat from tortured pigs raised in filthy conditions and join Safeway, Tim Hortons and McDonalds in taking a stand against the brutality of gestation crates. It will be better for the pigs and for your human customers.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elizabeth  Warkentin ","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3297145"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:51:27Z","content":"I watched the videos about the horrible ways these animals are treated especially the babies they have their heads bashed in to kill them and it doesn't, not instantly anyways. I have not eaten pork since watching this it's horrible treatment that should not be happening. Pigs are the most intelligent animal and they are kept in narrow and short gestation crates where they go crazy before they cruelly killed for our consumption. Please help them change how they treat these animals. I am not saying don't eat pork I am saying I am against unethical treatment!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lisa Bigstone","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25881736"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T19:30:24Z","content":"Animal cruelty should not exist.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mathieu Boileau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32681362"},{"created_at":"2013-05-13T00:00:13Z","content":"The pigs suffer a cruel life and it produces lower quality meat and lifestyles for these pigs.","like_count":0,"author_name":"logan smith","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/50394336"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T16:26:34Z","content":"I grew up on a farm and I love animals. I am not a vegetarian, but I strongly believe in the humane treatment of all animals.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Clayson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36372836"},{"created_at":"2013-04-06T12:28:50Z","content":"I lived on a farm before.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ryan Matthew","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/46584364"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T19:57:56Z","content":"why doesn't one of the westons or sobeys spend a day in one of these cages? see what it's like.","like_count":0,"author_name":"daisy morant","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36235222"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T21:19:59Z","content":"I've done ALL my shopping at superstore for the last 5 years of living on my own... I think I'm switching to Safeway and Costco now though. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Thammy Hendriks","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12002484"},{"created_at":"2012-12-27T00:33:57Z","content":"So much suffering for what? Your tastebuds? This just does not seem fair. Let's change things and make the world a bit better for the animals that have no choice but to give their LIVES to us. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Excedera St. Louis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/545971"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T23:29:12Z","content":"Reading about the horror 46257 suffered at the hands of a human make me sick! If this was done to a dog this person would be charged with animal abuse. How come it is legal to treat pigs this way?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Wheeler","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9791832"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T10:13:03Z","content":"i love all the animals","like_count":0,"author_name":"nancy ayotte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35185032"},{"created_at":"2012-12-12T02:51:09Z","content":"I'm a vegan and even though I disagree with killing animals to eat, the least human kind can do is let them live free and with good care until their death, which should be humane.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Geri Pilcher","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5088144"},{"created_at":"2013-05-02T20:22:12Z","content":"Absolutely disgusting ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Susan Lawton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/48615793"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T03:04:51Z","content":"This wrong on so many levels","like_count":0,"author_name":"Yvonne Bourque","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16981605"},{"created_at":"2012-12-24T02:53:07Z","content":"It is heartbreaking and sad to realize how poorly these animals are mistreated. More and more Canadians should be purchasing market shares from Community Supported Agriculture (CSA). Not only do you get farm fresh produce locally grown but they treat the animals they raise with dignity and respect. Mass production and confinement of animals is not appreciated.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Masse","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37206582"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:02:09Z","content":"It is shocking that Walmart claims to be a Christian company founded by Christians!  I wonder if all the \"Ch ristians\" who shop Walmart are aware of any of this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Edie Ninnis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12236943"},{"created_at":"2013-01-02T00:25:01Z","content":"Inhumane practices, such as, but not limited to, gestation cages, on factory 'farms' are a disgrace that have persisted for far too long. This should have ceased long ago and is not appropriate in ANY case. I, as a consumer and shopper for a family of five, have stopped buying meat from grocery stores for this reason.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha Young","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37819868"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T23:51:54Z","content":"I'm against any form of animal cruelty.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pradeep Goonetillake","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37109207"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T00:03:32Z","content":"All animals should be respected just as all humans should be respected.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Julie Wray","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29955932"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T01:45:02Z","content":"I am a human being with compassion","like_count":0,"author_name":"Penny Winestock","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37112302"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T18:47:09Z","content":"There is no excuse for the complete loss of compassion for these animals and the inhumanity of those who inflict such mindless cruelty.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelly Layton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1016197"},{"created_at":"2012-12-28T00:54:14Z","content":"Cruelty to any animal is unconscionable.  Good for you to care and make such an effort to expose this awful cruelty. What's wrong with human beings?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nan & Dianne Hartwick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/14616365"},{"created_at":"2013-04-02T10:48:55Z","content":"because animals matter just as much as PEOPLE","like_count":0,"author_name":"kennedy hill","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45955238"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T04:54:14Z","content":"Animals are sentient creatures. We are animals. We are doing this to ourselves.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maximilienne Ewalt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/928004"},{"created_at":"2013-04-02T11:05:46Z","content":"We stopped eating pork because of the barbaric treatment they receive.  We just felt like if we were still eating it knowing this was going on, then we were part of the problem.  It was around the same time as the \"swine-flu\" outbreak started.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rhonda Snow","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15700196"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:37:28Z","content":"Most people who saw this happening would want to change it. We musn't let ourselves become too distanced from the reality. We can change it, the animals can't. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ruth Danziger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8051874"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:05:35Z","content":"This is a very cruel way to treat an animal and I will not be buying any meat from any of the stores that purchase from these \"farms\" ","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Winter","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34924975"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T14:16:45Z","content":"i HATE  these crates for pigs.;  Would love to confine every single person working in places like this and see how they do.  Better still, dig a huge hole and push all the cruel people and close them up and walk away!  I absolutely abhor cruelty to innocent creatures!!!  Also the people who know about this and do nothing!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Virginia Greenwood-Warner","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1927820"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T19:55:29Z","content":"corporate farming is wrong on so many levels","like_count":0,"author_name":"Laurie MacKenzie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15896048"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T20:03:47Z","content":"I dont believe that animals should have to ever suffer to feed us humans, they derserve dignity!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Larry MacDonald","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25851178"},{"created_at":"2012-12-23T02:36:30Z","content":"Such acts of cruelty towards animals is sickening. It is heinous and I would love to see such treatments of animals be made illegal.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Guylaine San Filippo","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2671065"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T05:57:05Z","content":"I grew up on a farm and there is no need for this type of farming.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert Maksymetz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35920393"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T23:02:00Z","content":"I shop regularly at Superstore, however, I will no longer shop at your store until this practice is ended. I will only shop with chains that treat animals without cruelty.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Maggie Evans","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36247867"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T02:44:52Z","content":"Improper treatment of animals, even i they are for consumption is cruel. These animals are being bred and raised toward a dead end in life and humans should make their short lived lives ones with minimal suffering. I'm urging these industries to seek a more HUMANE methods and properly train their workers to follow those protocols,","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rocio Clara","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9997089"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T22:07:05Z","content":"Carol Exley","like_count":0,"author_name":"Carol Exley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25339736"},{"created_at":"2013-05-02T21:11:29Z","content":"Stop the torture, stop the murder!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Hahn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8328785"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T23:55:54Z","content":"Compassion is essential in all our dealings with other beings, we are one.  What we do to them we do to ourselves.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Barbara Chan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31277916"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T01:31:14Z","content":"It's animal cruelty and it's criminal. It should be punishable by law.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sacha Van De Putte","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36559972"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T14:14:44Z","content":"I will not eat pork again until this type of treatment of animals is banned as in Europe","like_count":0,"author_name":"Swain Valerie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21876307"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T15:16:42Z","content":"I love animals.  This is unbelievable how a human can abuse especially the innocent piglets.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Stacey Johnson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36289742"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T16:57:27Z","content":"It is UNBEARABLE !!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Catherine LHERICEL","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2486951"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T21:52:14Z","content":"No argument about \"your food rights\" could possibly justify such blatant and transparent cruelty...just look into this little creature's eyes...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sande McMullen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12844140"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:19:41Z","content":"Such an awful and terrible cruelty done to helpless pigs is HORROR PUR  for me and\r\na crime, which has to be punished hard. !!!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Irene WERNER","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1400871"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T22:43:18Z","content":"The quality of our food is affected by how a farmer treats his live stock the need for food makes us eat the pgis, there is no excuse for in human use of them! they are alive have feelings and if ppl understood they are used to save ppl even heart values, then they are due respect~!","like_count":0,"author_name":"wendy solomon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37106966"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T22:09:56Z","content":"because Pigs are magnificent sentient intelligent Beings, who deserve to live a happy full life, and not a nightmare of suffering and torture, just so some greedy heartless humans can have sausages and bacon for breakfast. CHANGE your diets, humans. Go Vegan! End Animal Cruelty NOW & 4EVER!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"I A","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2429944"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T11:14:19Z","content":"This is fucking sickening.","like_count":0,"author_name":"isak haapaniemi","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36996008"},{"created_at":"2013-04-03T20:53:25Z","content":"There needs to be a stop put to this horrific cruetly towards our non-human friends.  Although much more needs to be done, this is a definately a step in the right direction.","like_count":0,"author_name":"L.F. Gabber","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/43909077"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:30:40Z","content":"There is a better way.  Local farmers can be humane, have good products and make a profit.  No need to be cruel.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Annikki Desmarais","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35133752"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:11:15Z","content":"naturelle grow animals","like_count":0,"author_name":"David Blain-Curnick","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29323523"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T03:19:10Z","content":"This is unacceptable! How can we consider ourselves an intelligent society and then treat our animals like this?! This is unbelievable and must stop. The public must make it known that we don't support this type of industry!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tammy Shaw","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36192475"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:39:44Z","content":"Abuse of any kind should not be tolerated, period!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Diana Litshauer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7161636"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T13:12:26Z","content":"Pigs are intelligent beings, caring mothers, and feel pain just as we do. Please ensure they do not suffer in factory farms.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Debra Lawes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36359625"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T20:48:02Z","content":"I think we should do whats rite not profitable.","like_count":0,"author_name":"douglas black","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36544706"},{"created_at":"2012-12-15T14:27:48Z","content":"Animals are just like us: they have feelings, emotions, they feel pain, they need to move, to be with others, to eat and to have a certain freedom. We make them grow to finally kill them so we can eat meat. Fine. We do. But can we, at least, make them live their short life in respect and make them have at least a good life, where they won't suffer? We take the power to decide of their life and their death. Isn't it enough? Can't we just let them be \u00abhappy\u00bb the time we let them live? It won't cost more to let them live outside in gang than putting them in a cage, and anyways, you are making enough money to make the little sacrifice of having respect of their life.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Myriam Gari\u00e9py","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36646112"},{"created_at":"2013-03-28T20:26:58Z","content":"Would you want to live your life in one?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shayla Bond","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8984151"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T03:46:07Z","content":"Pigs are not only living creatures but smatrs ones too. No animal should deserve that treatment, but them even more so!","like_count":0,"author_name":"lyla dixon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37054285"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T05:25:23Z","content":"Why would anyone want to buy and eat the meat of animals raised cruelly.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Joanne McManus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15379962"},{"created_at":"2013-05-15T16:03:18Z","content":"Animal cruelty is horrific and no living creature deserves to be put through something as terrible as this. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Ferdily Brookelle","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29477869"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T17:22:07Z","content":"factory farming + processing is murder","like_count":0,"author_name":"Raymod Helkio","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10189834"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T21:17:35Z","content":"I'm disgusted that our government allows this to happen. It is beyond me to understand how a human being could be so cruel and work in this kind of environment, you could not pay me enough to do this day after day, year after year. All creatures, big and small deserve to live their lives without pain or anguish, this suffering must end!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Renee Brisson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1513917"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T02:09:22Z","content":"Every living creature deserves respect and dignity!! Its not humane to slaughter them for food but can we pls give them a little bit of painless life b4 u butcher them? ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Rowena Castaneda","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30638176"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T19:18:22Z","content":"Because your Christmas ham is not an entitlement, it's a gift. An animal that gives so much to us deserves to live a decent life.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nathan Langdon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26765600"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:12:09Z","content":"We need to be humane to animals and not subject them to pain and suffering. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Natasha George","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25950620"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:30:06Z","content":"Watching the W5 program brought to light the inhumane way these pigs are treated - people are questioning the way food is produced - I don't want to eat food where animals are cruelly kept - STOP BUYING FROM THESE DESPICABLE \"FARMS\"","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nina McMillan","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36250973"},{"created_at":"2013-01-15T19:16:42Z","content":"Animal torture and suffering is intolerable. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brett Kane","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38675210"},{"created_at":"2012-12-25T01:16:00Z","content":"Animals can think and feel just as much as humans and the fact that they are allowed to be treated like this was is nothing less than sickening. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mike Mulders","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22064744"},{"created_at":"2013-03-30T04:56:41Z","content":"I care about animals","like_count":0,"author_name":"maria hadjiapostoli","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31310161"}]}
