asy to say to eat meat is okay if youre not standing on the cutting side of the knife.  Place yourself in the shoes of the pig for one day, or as a human place yourself in the shoes of a prisoner, stuck in a 2 x 2 cell (innocently) waiting execution.  This is what this pig and many others like her have to go through before they brutally murdered and slaughtered for ham, bacon, chops. How can humans evene think something like this is acceptable in an enlightened world.  If you want to eat a pig, at least allow her fresh air, good food and room to breathe and walk around.  When you kill her, please handle her with care and do it quick so that she doesnt suffer, since pig farmers WONT stop producing pigs for the cannibalistic meat market. I was a meat eater once myself.  But have stopped, when the reality of what these animals have to go through to land on my place hit me in the face.  PLEASE STOP THIS CRUELTY AND CHANGE YOUR CRUELTY TO KINDNESS.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Elsje Massyn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6719713"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T02:58:23Z","content":"I am a food writer and chef. My life's passion revolves around educating others about food that comes from safe, healthy sources... free of antibiotics, hormones, pesticides, GMO's and cruelty. Please STOP this. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kristen Wiwczaruk","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36491705"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:49:32Z","content":"This practice is absolutely crazy! It's hard to believe we humans can subject other living creatures to such horrific conditions. Shame on us! Please rectify this situation. Please.","like_count":0,"author_name":"John Taylor","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11268796"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T23:52:36Z","content":"This sort of treatment is unnecessary. I am a meat-eater... and I prefer to purchase my meat from humane sources.  To that end, I won't be purchasing pork products from my local Metro.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Tr