pi.change.org/u/31908841"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:28:46Z","content":"Yes, its alright for the pig growers to kill pigs for food stores, but not to torment them first! That is darn cruel for any animal of any kind! As for me, i do not eat meat just for that reason of slaughtering these animals, as i do not like to see any animal killed just for the pleasure of people eating the meat! So, i am glad some one is doing their job and trying to stop this tormenting of animals! Thank you,,,Margurette Asselstine,,","like_count":0,"author_name":"Margurette Asselstine","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33051558"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:34:45Z","content":"Animals need to be treated humanely and shouldn't be treated cruelly before slaughter.  Also this type of industrialized raising of animals is terrible for the environment and for humans!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Felicia Brooker","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33843342"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:41:00Z","content":"This brief report will haunt me forever. I now will never eat pork and I am considering ceasing shopping ever again at these retailers: Sobeys, Superstore/Loblaws, Metro and Walmart Canada. I will never pass the meat aisle again without remembering what I saw and read here.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Nadia Abu-Zahra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23505705"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:47:47Z","content":"We should all stop eating pork completely, but since not everyone agrees, the least we can do is make sure pigs aren't being tortured.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Edith Sinclair","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7379470"}]}
