name":"maria munoz","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36972857"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T03:51:46Z","content":"I HATE ANIMAL CRUELTY","like_count":1,"author_name":"BRENDA FUSSELL","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24651893"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T00:37:47Z","content":"This has to be stopped and we can help do that.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Sandra MacNevin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17142675"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T03:06:07Z","content":"I believe those who insist on eating meat should eat healthy ones. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Patrick LeBlanc","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24184923"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T13:24:02Z","content":"It is one of the worst and inhuman things I have seen in my whole life,even the way they transport them in those Iron Cages hitting against the bars and hurting it is a shame! I would say shame on those traders!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alberto Rojas","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36584799"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T03:18:15Z","content":"Please put into place humane procedures. We owe it to the animals.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Paul Durber","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36972380"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T22:13:21Z","content":"No animal should suffer like this.  There are definitely more humane ways.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Marie Ren\u00e9 de Cotret","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17121173"},{"created_at":"2012-12-16T17:29:12Z","content":"unnecessary animal cruelty, which includes other animals used for human consumption","like_count":1,"author_name":"karin brezinka","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36700312"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:51:47Z","content":"This should not be allowed.  I will not buy pork from these stores.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ethel Sivilotti","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36968848"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T14:04:14Z","content":"This is unnecessary cruelty and should be stopped immediately.  The organizations that profit from this need to be boycotted.  There are humane and civilized ways to treat this creatures.  This is a shame for the entire human race.","like_count":1,"author_name":"ivy mason","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17157024"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T20:56:08Z","content":"Because being human means caring about all animals not just the human ones.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Eron Chorney","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28130171"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T18:57:51Z","content":"All creatures deserve humane treatment","like_count":1,"author_name":"D T","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30022667"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T01:37:05Z","content":"It makes me sick to my stomach that humans can treat such beautiful and gentle creatures so horribly, they are going to be killed, let them live their short lives in comfort, this is just barbaric.  These poor babies. :(\r\n ","like_count":1,"author_name":"diana baugh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20768396"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T04:15:09Z","content":"I hate unnecessary cruelty towards any living feeling creature. It is reprehensible for humans to behave so inhumanely. End this now.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Lisa Ross","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36974976"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T13:52:27Z","content":"Unimaginable. Is it necessary to torture an animal in order to eat? I will not buy any meat products from Sobeys, Loblaws, Metro, or Walmart until I read that you have asked suppliers to phase out use of gestation crates.","like_count":1,"author_name":"terry teskey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12175714"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:17:58Z","content":"I stopped buying pork over ten years ago for this very reason. I cannot eat something that has been so badly treated. The misery screams into my enjoyment of the food. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Allison Bishop","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15466790"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T04:50:59Z","content":"Gestation cages are not the way to go. And we owe that much to the pigs for providing food for us; we have to show our sympathy in respect. Let them live in peace rather than in torture  before their time. We are capable of good change with some investment in housing systems. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Linda Do","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36340159"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T21:20:19Z","content":"Humans are disgusting and I hope this changes someday.","like_count":1,"author_name":"JB Bohorquez","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36781814"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T21:03:41Z","content":"Pigs are intelligent animals. Given a chance they are clean and social. To treat any animal like industry swine takes away from our own humanity.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Barbara McPherson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23233899"},{"created_at":"2013-03-26T12:35:26Z","content":"Pigs are social, curious and intelligent. It is a stain on our humanity that we treat these sentient beings with such cruelty.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jenn Sorrell","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26888793"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:17:19Z","content":"no animal should suffer for our needs. We need to do better.","like_count":1,"author_name":"alan sleightholme","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29920902"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T19:13:18Z","content":"These farms inflicting so much pain on these highly intelligent animals should be put out of business and owners jailed!  ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Josee Sansoucy","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24241969"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T00:38:57Z","content":"These animals make the ultimate sacrifice already. It gives me no pleasure to know they also have to suffer during their brief life as well.  As a consumer I know I have the choice and will exercise this right accordingly.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Beata Rancourt","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31230722"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:10:06Z","content":"I stopped eating meat,poultry,etc 40 years ago.  I don't believe any animal should be abused whether it is to be killed for food.  I do object to greed,cruelty where abuse is encouraged","like_count":1,"author_name":"Jean Corsini","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1133252"},{"created_at":"2012-12-27T04:08:57Z","content":"I am a meat-eater and am still digusted when I hear stories such as these. I grew up on a farm and I know that animals are healthier and even taste better when they live as close to a natural life as possible. Many of the farms in Southern Ontario are now abandoned and it is not considered a viable way to make a living. As a result we get mass-produced animals fed on a diet of chemicals and growth hormones which we then transfer into our own bodies. And to the corporate greedheads who perpetuate this system, the suffering of the animals themselves is not even a consideration","like_count":1,"author_name":"mike mackinnon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16399463"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:52:19Z","content":"No animal needs to suffer.  Stop meat consumption, there are other protein sources.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Antoinette Engel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/21394352"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T12:45:51Z","content":"Pigs are intelligent animals and shouldn't be treated like this.  It's bad enough that we kill them for food but must we torture them too?","like_count":1,"author_name":"Kim Harding","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36583095"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T04:04:21Z","content":"This is horrific, only eat ethically grown meat!!!!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Zabrina Nelson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31001127"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T14:15:19Z","content":"Humans need to stop profiting off of the misery of their fellow earthlings.  If you can't conduct a business wihtout torture then you shouldn't be in business.","like_count":1,"author_name":"steve usatis","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27000204"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T21:03:56Z","content":"This is no life for any animal to endure. These cages must go, I'd happily pay more for pork know it was raised humanely.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Clark Webb","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31132288"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T00:10:35Z","content":"I detest cruelty to both humans and animals","like_count":1,"author_name":"Michael Brockway","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29731957"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T00:38:20Z","content":"After the airing of W5 (pig farm) I wow th never eat or buy prok ever .I am contemplating on becoming a vegetarian.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Donald Rochon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36183995"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T19:30:21Z","content":"Because I can't stand violence of any kind on any living being.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alexandra Konstantinidou","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8748371"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T03:19:19Z","content":"Look into the eyes of this dear pig and not weep!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Maureen Wallace","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/6839094"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T00:55:25Z","content":"I have seen and helped care for a few pigs in my life.  I went to a large pig farm in my adulthood and was rather saddened to see how they were being held.  NOW, 40 years later, I remember playing with a Large boar in his dirty old pen, and we 5 kids were riding him and playing with him, and he was enjoying it. I have also held baby piglets, and played with older ones, and was surprised to see the intelligence shown by each pig.  The like to be clean, but outside, the mud on their body helps keep parasites and flies off them.  I have worked with the small Vietnanese Pigs when they first became popular.  It was sad to see people who knew nothing really about animal care take these little animals home, housebreak them, love them, and then get them so fat they won't keep them!  PIGS are teachable, trainable animals, they feel kind of funny to the touch, but they love being scratched like a dog.  Treat them with the care and respect ALL  animals are due!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nedene Vere","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23032539"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T02:17:33Z","content":"This practice is inhumane.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Sindy Milosevich","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11525614"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T04:26:59Z","content":"they are our relatives,-empathy !!","like_count":1,"author_name":"carl schoener","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35666700"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T04:02:42Z","content":"I will skip the '' i am shocked '' part because i think everyone is. I have taken the decision on Sunday December 9th, to not eat meat anymore. I can only blame myself to have not seen earlier in my existence the pain and suffering that you are inflicting to these poor animals, that only wants to be loved in return In a way, i am very happy that this Company and its employees got caught on tape, and broadcasted on television, so that the whole world could see.\r\n\r\nWhat i was more disgusted at is to see your employees actually having fun doing it !!! And please do not tell the public that it is not true, because its just IS. I seriously felt like throwing up in front of my television. \r\n\r\nTo end this short letter of opinion, the only thing that i wish is for that company to close down, or to go bankrupt, and to be forced to close. I also wish for our Canadian government to act upon this, and to re-enforce its laws, and to take example like in the United Kingdom. There, a person can do a prison sentence of 51 months, and also has to pay a 20 000 $ fine. I also wish for big companies like Wal Mart, Metro, and others mentionned to wake up.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Benoit Cousineau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36554087"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:03:55Z","content":"Can't believe this type of thing still happens!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Rob Condon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24424304"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T20:41:40Z","content":"This just wrong, lets put an end to factory farming!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Karin Condon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8827780"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T21:20:43Z","content":"They give us so much, let's give them some respect.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Paul Johnston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35101717"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T20:04:02Z","content":"I used to keep pigs ,they are intelligent feeling sentient animals,even if you eat meat,there is no need for this sort of cruelty, as an aside,stressed animals do NOT make good meat! IT IS TOTALLY UNECESSARY,pay a bit extra and get a better meal,and pigs lives are no longer a misery!!!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Val Matthews","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29576953"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:04:00Z","content":"All living feeling animals should live without suffering","like_count":1,"author_name":"june williams","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35854023"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T00:14:06Z","content":"My heart is broken.  I cannot believe in a society like Canada/US we are allowing this to happen.  We are educated...at least I thought we were.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Erma Rogers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36182353"},{"created_at":"2012-12-16T16:51:24Z","content":"Cruelty and indifference to the well-being of animals who nourish us is immoral, inhumane, diminishes us all and yet again demonstrates why we are the scourge of this planet.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Maryann Shemansky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7499287"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T04:49:36Z","content":"There is no justification possible for torturing any living creature. If this treatment was done to a pet, it would be deemed as cruelty towards animals and punishable under Canadian Law!!","like_count":1,"author_name":"A. Valent","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36728898"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T02:17:56Z","content":"I will keep in mind the grocery chains that buy from these factory farms and will absolutely NOT purchase until this situation changes...THere are many other stores out there...that these Chains would buy from this factory farm demonstrates their attitude, lack of compassion, greed, and demonstrates that they care only for the bottom line...I am sure to pass this on to anyone that I know whether friends or clubs that I belong too...I will be waiting to hear that no more pork is purchased from this disgraceful and disgusting factory farm...SHAME ON YOU!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Anne Kaufmann","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13500127"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T10:53:40Z","content":"This is sick and cruel","like_count":1,"author_name":"Carrie Solomon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/13218421"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T18:44:23Z","content":"Pigs are sentient beings on the same level as three year old humans.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Michael Munger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36388633"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:04:32Z","content":"Because cruelty toward any creature is disgusting, saddening, sickening and unacceptable. I know slaughter is a necessary part of raising animals for food but we must accept only the most humane possible treatment at every stage of the lives they give for us. Punishment for torturing an animal should be SEVERE!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Tamara Raeburn","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36966958"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T05:08:54Z","content":"I shall not shop in your store  knowing that these unforunate animals are treated so unspeakably. Please reconsider and change their keep AND their KEEPERS so that your store can be proud. Do it so you won't have regrets in the future! Thanks, Dorothy","like_count":1,"author_name":"Dorothy Ogonovsky","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36340775"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:04:33Z","content":"people are to greedy for money.. and dont care about animal welfare.. this must stop","like_count":1,"author_name":"yazz eddinton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10742918"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T01:34:31Z","content":"These pigs are not brain dead! They have needs, physical and emotional. Pigs are as and more intelligent than dogs. How can any decent person put these poor animals through this abuse and even torture? Answer - They can't, at least no decent human. Imagine an existence that is solely that, existence. My heart goes out to these animals that never asked to be born, and are helpless and totally dependent on the kindness of man. And these animals have far more sensitivity and even humanity than any owner/operator/worker that is responsible for this atrocity. That means, anyone in the business. You don't deserve the kindness that these animals deserve.  ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Suzanne Sheldon","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/24207085"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T22:23:30Z","content":"They are living beings that feel pain. It is all very disgusting when people feel no empathy!!!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Susan  Grandberg","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3554697"},{"created_at":"2012-12-08T23:35:28Z","content":"It is about time we started looking after the animals properly.  They are living, breathing creatures.  ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Shelley Mottershead","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/5060354"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T14:22:15Z","content":"I shop regularly at Sobey's and Loblaws in Toronto, but will (a) be raising this with local store managers on my next visits, and (b) will shift my purchases to other grocery stores unless they stop this torture.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Richard Elliott","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10750012"},{"created_at":"2012-12-16T17:43:35Z","content":"I challenge all animal cruelty.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Adrian Appley","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/3318072"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T21:16:32Z","content":"just because animals do not have a voice doesnt mean they deserve or like to be abused","like_count":1,"author_name":"Danielle Deneault","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25629709"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T01:53:56Z","content":"THIS IS BEYOND CRUEL...","like_count":1,"author_name":"DIANE HANVEY","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36968939"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T19:48:33Z","content":"Farming practices need to be humane and respectful of the animals enduring a life of slavery and lack of freedom. Many have lost sight of that..","like_count":1,"author_name":"Heather Kerr-Vermeulen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27187805"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T12:36:06Z","content":"I grew up on a family farm where animals were treated well even when they ended up on the dinner table.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Sandra Stemmler","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36745112"},{"created_at":"2013-03-23T19:36:34Z","content":"To sin by silence when one must protest makes cowards of men.\r\n When we turn our back on the helpless, when we fail to speak on behalf of the voiceless, when we tolerate animal abuse and animal suffering, then the moral compass of a just and compassionate society is gone.\r\n...Abraham Lincoln","like_count":1,"author_name":"Maria Vickers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/45072147"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T04:53:27Z","content":"I am sick and tired of any form of animal cruelty","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nikki Odehnal","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/10433305"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T20:50:01Z","content":"Raising animals for meat can be done ethically. As a consumer I demand animal welfare be considered in the meat industry","like_count":1,"author_name":"Cody Dey","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36370354"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T23:44:19Z","content":"because they are practiseing animal abuse and toture on the p