 a bad day or a pig was not cooperating they would just kill a pig for no reason and how no one there cared for the well- being of these animals. It made  my partner feel like he was worthless, he got really depressed and was always upset with his life and the consent daily killing. He would come home and take it out on his family. Finally he had to go on Medical Stress leave and eventually got his doctor to say that he was not allowed to go to work in a place of this manner. I believe that every animal out there be pig, cow or chicken be kept in cages that are big enough for them and be able to have free- roam time. The things that go on in these places are horrifying and cruel and need to be stopped, not just for the animals but for the people that work there as well!","like_count":0,"author_name":"heather cormier","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26942016"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T14:28:24Z","content":"Because our current methods of food production are not sustainable and are ruining our environment!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Danielle Rolfe","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15128408"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T22:35:05Z","content":"Cruelty has consequnces on the mental health of the workers, our health and the inccocent animals - who deserve to be treated with respect - they are living creatures.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karin Freihammer","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/33662417"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T15:26:19Z","content":"cruelty to animals is disgraceful. you know about the practice and continue to NOT CARE? Walmart is disgusting and I will never shop there. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"wendy nash","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31099127"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T17:33:46Z","content":"Animal rights now. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"joe Wilford","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9876906"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T14:17:14Z","content":"Animal abuse is never OK- the farming industry is abusive to animals. We ar