h Canadian family and the practice of allowing these heinous acts of cruelty on animals in our food chain instills shame on my Canadian connection and ancestry. The issue is not that these animals die as part of a country\u2019s food chain\u2014the issue is how they are treated beforehand. Several issues occur when these animals live in these painful and unhealthy conditions; confinement and overcrowding of these animals result in taxed immune systems which are less able to cope with infections and disease. The large concentration of animals, animal waste, and the potential for dead animals in such small space also poses serious health issues, increasing the risk of transmitting food-borne illnesses to the humans who are consuming these animals.  As Mahatma Gandhi once reflected, \"The measure of a society can be how well its people treat its animals.\"  Please show the rest of the world that Canada has the integrity to end these egregious practices.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Savona Holmes","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/179813"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T14:59:53Z","content":"Senseless killing","like_count":0,"author_name":"Bruce Langos","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9878173"},{"created_at":"2012-12-19T23:39:54Z","content":"There is no excuse why any animal should have to be treated so inhumanely I'm appauled at the heartless workers there..disgusting!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Mancel","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/17343133"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T16:50:26Z","content":"Walmart---the global reach of your hegemony will not protect you from the exposure of the internet outing of your brutal supply line \"contractors\"   Wake up and change your business","like_count":0,"author_name":"susan  rudnicki","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/815386"},{"created_at":"2012-12-14T16:07:40Z","content":"It is important to me because animals should not be treated this way. It is disgusting.. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kelsey Watton"