ling creatures.  They feel pain.  They feel sadness.  They feel grief. You wouldn't do this to a dog, why would you to a pig.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sharon Speck","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37042442"},{"created_at":"2013-04-22T20:53:38Z","content":"terrible video...","like_count":0,"author_name":"Daniel Coelho","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/39063521"},{"created_at":"2013-01-05T14:50:57Z","content":"I like to make my choices through consumer action (ie not buying a certain product).  But if I don't know how that product is produced, I am left with no other option but to sign a petition.  Is there any way we can get labels on our food to tell us how it was produced?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Greg Fenty","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34064837"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T00:15:39Z","content":"These pigs are beings with the precious life force energy we humans have. All life should be honoured and respected. Many humans do not realize the karma they incure from treating other forms of life in this manner, and thus they will incure an uncomfortable life for themselves. When we honour life we in turn are honoured with a better life. Humans need to understand this.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lori Moss","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/945277"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T03:26:59Z","content":"I do not want animals to live a miserable life so I can eat cheap meat.  I don't even want to eat the meat of an animal that has lived in misery.  Not only is this unnecessary, we now know that the energy of the animal is in the meat that we eat... and we think that this misery is OK to feed to our families? It is not true that this is necessary to feed the masses. We do not need to do this.  Not only pigs are raised in misery but cows and poultry as well. I already refuse to buy any of it and I voice this opinion whenever I can.\r\n","like_count":0,"author_name":"Marianne Ferguson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37053637"},{"crea