"voula spyropoulos","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37105539"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T22:40:09Z","content":"Animal cruelty is sick .. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brittany Houston","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/22805998"},{"created_at":"2013-01-02T07:19:19Z","content":"this is critically important to me, how we treat animals is arcane, cruel and barbaric. I do not shop at those stores and have stopped eating meat after watching a video of how animals are slaughtered. If you want to get Wal Mart's attention, write to the Walton family foundation directly. Humans are the most dangerous animals, act now.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Louise Boutin","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37827963"},{"created_at":"2013-02-05T02:10:12Z","content":" To:\r\nMarc Poulin, President & CEO, Sobeys\r\nFran\u00e7ois Vimard, Executive Vice-President, Sobeys\r\nDavid Smith, Vice-President of Sustainability, Sobeys\r\nGalen G. Weston, Executive Chairman, Loblaws\r\nVicente Trius, President, Loblaws\r\nRobert Chant, Senior Vice-President, Corporate Affairs & Communication, Loblaws\r\nEric R. La Fl\u00e8che, President & Chief Executive Officer, Metro\r\nRobert Sawyer, Executive VP & Chief Operating Officer, Metro\r\nShelley Broader, Chief Executive Officer, Walmart Canada\r\nBob Hakeem, Senior Vice-President, People, Walmart Canada\r\nAndrew Pelletier, Vice-President, Corporate Affairs & Sustainability, Walmart Canada\r\nLee Tappenden, Chief Merchandizing Officer, Walmart Canada\r\nDear Decision-Makers,\r\n\r\nI was shocked and horrified by the animal abuse recently documented on hidden camera by Mercy For Animals Canada at one of your pork suppliers \u2013 Puratone. Meat from these abused animals is currently being sold in your stores under the Maple Leaf Foods and Freybe brands of pork.\r\n\r\nI am disgusted to see how pregnant pigs are kept locked in narrow, metal gestation crates barely larger than their own bodies. In such intensive and unrelenting confinement, these intelligent and social animals are unable to even turn around, lie down comfortably, walk, or engage in other basic behaviours.\r\n\r\nRecognizing their inherent cruelty, many of your major competitors have started demanding that their pork suppliers do away with gestation crates \u2013 including Safeway, McDonalds, Tim Hortons and over 30 other major retailers in Canada and the United States\r\n\r\nIt's time for your company to take a stand against egregious animal abuse by requiring all of your pork suppliers to phase out gestation crates.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and consideration.\r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\n[Jennifer S] ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jennifer Simmons","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30656890"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T03:02:02Z","content":"liberty","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Tremblay","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36335344"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T14:56:04Z","content":"The same drive for profit that yields animal cruelty, yields poor treatment of employees, and ultimately poor treatment of even customers.  There is no separation.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Mark Rosenau","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37136391"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:40:08Z","content":"Because if no one does anything then the humanity and integrity of our food supply will continue. It's not anyone else's fault but our own if we allow it to continue.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jason Froats","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16254214"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T21:09:21Z","content":"I eat pork and I don't want the poor animals suffering for that or I will stop.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindy Drew-Tsang","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37035978"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T21:52:32Z","content":"We need to respect the animals that feed us.","like_count":0,"author_name":"scott bihari","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36323067"}]}
