can all agree that raising animals for consumption in a more humane way is better for the animals, better for the people who care for them, and better for the people who eat them. More humane farming practices mean that farmers don't have to use antibiotics as extensively, and as we are reminded all too frequently, agricultural antibiotic use can be dangerous, creating antibiotic resistance that can transfer to human pathogens. In many other cases, farmers have found that humane rearing practices make their animals more productive, and consumers are generally glad to know that the animal they are about to eat lived a pain-free life that more closely approximated its natural thriving. Please, please do not reward these cruel and unsustainable practices with your business. Use of gestation crates is bad farming and bad business, and totally beneath the dignity of a nation that is otherwise so enlightened. Please take leadership on this issue. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jacob Foster","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36296747"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T17:16:22Z","content":"because all life are precious","like_count":0,"author_name":"neveu charlene","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36298028"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T18:30:43Z","content":"Modern factory farming practices are cruel and inhumane. They are just as immoral as slavery once was. That practice was also legal at one time, but no one would defend it today. Grocery stores that buy animal products from factory farms are guilty of causing great harm and suffering to helpless, intelligent, social animals. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Vicki Van Linden","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/19900873"},{"created_at":"2013-01-21T15:20:58Z","content":"We human have no right to control and hurt animals the way we do, we are getting inhuman day by day.. this kind of activities should be stopped.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Abhishek Kumar","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36471886"},{"created_at"