2-12-20T17:44:31Z","content":"Because the cruelty animals reared for human consumption undergo is absolutely unnecessary. To meet the same demands, those who make their living raising and slaughtering these animals can do so without such cruelty. And why wouldn't they? This story is a pathetic testimony of a human being's capability for cruelty. This is the stuff of the Dark Ages. Sickening. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Shannen Leigh","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26501252"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:10:53Z","content":"It is disgusting that these and other animals are treated this way and kept in such horrible conditions.  It breaks my heart and angers me so much that people can let this go on!  Please stop supporting this!!!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Andrea Kostyra","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28364386"},{"created_at":"2012-12-22T20:16:27Z","content":"STOP!!! Cruel beyond belief. Not reasonable. In fact, completely insane.","like_count":0,"author_name":"isabelle rousset","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/1505665"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T19:29:00Z","content":"This is an inhumane practice that we all can do without.  Please stop!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen  Tate","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23298157"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T21:20:52Z","content":"the  drugs  required  to  keep  this  animal  alive and able  to  grow  in  these conditions enter  our  water supplies  and  our bodies. antiibiotic resistant bacteria have evolved beyond our ability  to  contain them  in hospitals. This methood  of  raising meat creates  ideal  conditions  for  new  drug resistant  diseases to  arrise. Pigs  are close  enough  to  humans for   the crossover of diseases to  people to occur. factory farming  animals,with high density crowded conditions,low  exercise,little air ,drug treatments in thier food and  medications  when deseased individuals  can  be preserved  long  enough  for  slaughter and shipping  creates  an  ideal  enviroment  for  developing  pathological  germs  and  bacteria. This  is  not  a way  to  have  a  safe   food  supply","like_count":0,"author_name":"andrew st john","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/25355082"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T19:17:03Z","content":"Actually, just who are the animals?","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gwen Romani","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2307690"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T04:53:02Z","content":"We work so hard for the companion animal issues,the real suffering is in the meat industry.This poor soul would love to have as all part of life.People who eat meat live in denial.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Karen Cleland","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/27537974"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T05:22:44Z","content":"I have an affinity to pigs and all creatures. No animal should be tortured.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Janet Selinger","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37057526"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T19:27:05Z","content":"I was on vacation once, at a ranch, staying with my parents in a cute little trailer/cabin. They went for a hike, I stayed behind to sit on the porch and read while I played with some kittens. Two biiig sows came from opposite sides of the cabin and started snuffling my hair and generally harassing me. I do love animals, so we played for a few minutes before a thunderstorm moved in and it was so violent that the rain was sideways, the sky was as dark as I've ever seen it, and you could see each lightning fork. I grabbed the kitten and ran inside the cabin. I heard a noise and turned around to see both sows standing nervously in the kitchenette area. You've never seen pigs look so big, or a kitchenette look so small. They were both scared, comforting each other and staring at me. Finally, one of them stepped forward and leaned her head against me, like she was concerned that I was scared like she and her friend were. I wasn't scared, of course, but I hugged her head and scratched her ears until the other sow came over to snuggle as well. The storm was over as soon as it started, and as I checked out the window to see what the weather was doing, I heard the door swing open, and turned to watch the duo let themselves out, casting bit doe-eyed smiles back at me. I love and respect all animals, but animals that show me compassion... It leaves a mark. People are outraged by puppy-mills, so it is utterly beyond my comprehension that torturing pigs in far worse ways is just fine. A \"turn the other way\" situation. All for the great god bacon, at that. No animal deserves to be treated the way they are at factory farms. Just because they \"taste good\" doesn't mean it's okay to turn a blind eye to their suffering before they end up in your double cheeseburger.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Allysen Dupler","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36538948"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T20:50:52Z","content":"I cannot begin to say how disgusted I am, yet again, by the inhumane treatment of animals in this country. Please sign this petition.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lindsey Huculiak","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/26806675"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T14:15:35Z","content":"I find it difficult to digest someone treating another life form in such a cruel manner.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Parul Hindocha","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23418880"},{"created_at":"2013-01-01T15:07:19Z","content":"We know better damn it!!!!! ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Teri Henderson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37804815"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T14:13:11Z","content":"There must not be any cruelty among humanity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sergey Cheremnov","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36285754"},{"created_at":"2012-12-10T14:36:37Z","content":"Animals that serve as food need to be treated with dignity.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kerri Balaton","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36287205"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T00:17:18Z","content":"I am trul