_name":"sylvain di battista","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36344413"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T15:42:59Z","content":"That some are capable of inflicting cruelty on powerless beings means that we are all capable of doing so under the right conditions.  This means that as a species, as a society, we must be vigilant for the sets of circumstances that bring about our ability to ignore cruelty, which are usually economically driven.  I do not eat meat in protest against treatment such as this.  I refrain most especially from eating factory raised animals, as this degrades not only the victims of it, innocent and powerless animals, but also degrades ourselves that we can let it happen, all in order to have bacon on the plate.  Bacon on the plate and the 'Canadian' way of life, which simply put, means entitlement.  We are not entitled to eat meat.  We are not entitled to inflict cruetly, these are constructs of our culture that we have somehow learned to push aside, never question and never feel.  We must learn to feel again or it will be our downfall in the end. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Abigail Watkins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/12384222"},{"created_at":"2012-12-17T21:12:23Z","content":"The government supports what the public denies. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"William Lalonde","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29456760"},{"created_at":"2012-12-09T03:04:53Z","content":"Animal cruelty must stop!  My husband and I were both raised on a farm but have stopped eating meat for over a year now .  We can no longer participate in this abuse of animals by supporting the meat industry.  Our children and their families are also begininnig to question todays farming practices.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Beattie","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/9401600"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:27:09Z","content":"There are more humane was to do this. The impact this has right now on children who have seen this on TV is great, let alone the adu