ly support them. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Kaleigh McIntyre","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34478347"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T21:39:21Z","content":"Because what they are doing is wrong. They tell people it's fresh when really there just being cruel. This is not right! Take a stand!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Chloe Hofmann","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/34126375"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T22:56:34Z","content":"While there is nothing wrong with killing animals for consumption, it is very wrong to abuse and torture them. The suffering they endure is inhuman and pointless. The pain and suffering they endure also ends up in our stomachs. . Please, stop that monstrosity!","like_count":0,"author_name":"Cendrine Marrouat","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/37042661"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T23:19:52Z","content":"It appalls me that any sentient creature be treated this one, especially an animal as intelligent as the domestic pig. I know that I, as a meat eater, am complicit in this process and will make a commitment to become a more mindful consumer. It would be very heartening to see major retailers to do the same in order to minimize this cruelty. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sarah Lee","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/29804753"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T01:10:38Z","content":"Wow, I do not want to buy pork any more. Very sad state of affairs, how on earth can these produces live with themselves.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Robert Emerson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/7278820"},{"created_at":"2012-12-21T05:22:47Z","content":"Get your facts straight!! Sows in loose housing cause more damage to each other from fighting than when they are in containment stalls.Give the sow a choice and she will pick the stall where it is quiet and safe.A pig is an animal not a human and as such acts in the animal kingdom world ,not in our human world.These are not pets ,they are animals raising pork for your kitchen tables.Get your facts s