s_to.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.hsi.org/assets/pdfs/hsi-fa-white-papers/economics_of_alternatives_to.pdf</a>","like_count":0,"author_name":"Paul Youngman","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/30109318"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:04:24Z","content":"It is unethical to increase profits by keeping animals in cruel conditions.  I no longer buy pork in any form.  ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Gregory Nicholls","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/20698547"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:29:40Z","content":"It's inhumane and of course a disgusting way to raise livestock.","like_count":0,"author_name":"George Pres","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/35018969"},{"created_at":"2012-12-13T04:47:13Z","content":"The video of the pigs being tortured and killed inhumanely is disguisting. I'm all for eating meat, especially pork, but if an animal is going to be slaughtered for food, if must be quick and painless. This animal cruelty needs to stop.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Brent Cherry","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/15962637"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T16:55:04Z","content":"It seems logical that as creatures of the sun we should only ingest creatures who have actually lived in the sun, eaten healthy natural food, and lived happy lives. They are what they eat, we are what we eat. Simple principle. Eating tortured animals means eating terror, stress, and disease. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Michelle van Kampen","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/11115251"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T17:35:38Z","content":"This is one small, first step in demanding an end to factory farming and all the torture, cruelty and apathy that goes with it!  Future generations will look back and wonder what was wrong with us as a society.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lorraine Watson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/2489040"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:55:49Z","content":"Anyone with a conscience would know this is wrong.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Sam Mahin","autho