or everyone.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Lucy Collins","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/31620321"},{"created_at":"2012-12-11T13:48:18Z","content":"Je suis contre la cruaut\u00e9 envers les animaux.","like_count":0,"author_name":"Pierre Baril","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/36361793"},{"created_at":"2013-01-18T04:05:22Z","content":"I have been a vegetarian for a little over two years now, and seeing this horrific and gut-wrenching practice reminds me of why made the decision to stop eating meat. These animals do not exist solely for our exploitation, torture, and sadistic lust for consuming flesh. I am honored to be one less individual contributing to this heinous and disgusting process. ","like_count":0,"author_name":"Scott Pickett","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/38869719"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T18:43:14Z","content":"I humanely raise sheep","like_count":0,"author_name":"Jocelyn Angus","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/32972229"},{"created_at":"2012-12-20T20:13:53Z","content":"WLhLlis this important to you? (Optional)","like_count":0,"author_name":"Linda Hanson","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/28161431"},{"created_at":"2012-12-18T04:59:10Z","content":"Over 100 years ago, we used to make children work in factories, coal mines, etc., etc. Sometimes parents would take their children to the local madhouse to watch the \"crazy\" people. And everyone thought that this was normal and acceptable. We have evolved far past this acceptance of human cruelty. It's now time to realize that these animals are sentient creatures who share many emotions that people do. Allowing this horrific cruelty to continue puts you and other corporate leaders in the ranks of other apologists for the sort of abysmal cruelty that used to routinely happen to other humans in our not-so-distant past. Yeah, maybe it's more expensive to raise animals humanely, but I do believe that the majority of consumers would support a price increase in meat costs. Look at how, af